import plotly.graph_objects as go

fig = go.Figure()

# Add stock price line
fig.add_trace(go.Scatter(
    x=rbc_reset['Date'],
    y=rbc_reset['Close_RY.TO'],
    mode='lines',
    name='RBC Close Price',
    line=dict(color='royalblue')
))

# Add economic events
for date, label in events.items():
    fig.add_vline(x=pd.to_datetime(date), line_width=1, line_dash="dot", line_color="red")
    fig.add_annotation(
        x=pd.to_datetime(date),
        y=rbc_reset['Close_RY.TO'].max() * 0.95,
        text=label,
        showarrow=True,
        arrowhead=1,
        ax=0,
        ay=-40,
        font=dict(size=9, color="red"),
        textangle=90
    )

# Layout
fig.update_layout(
    title='Royal Bank of Canada (RY.TO) Stock Price with Economic Events: 20042024',
    xaxis_title='Date',
    yaxis_title='Price (CAD)',
    hovermode='x unified',
    template='plotly_white',
    width=1100,
    height=600
)

fig.show()

import plotly.graph_objects as go
import pandas as pd

# Create the figure
fig = go.Figure()

# Add stock price line
fig.add_trace(go.Scatter(
    x=rbc_reset['Date'],
    y=rbc_reset['Close_RY.TO'],
    mode='lines',
    name='RBC Close Price',
    line=dict(color='royalblue')
))

# Add vertical lines and annotations for events
for date, label in events.items():
    fig.add_vline(x=pd.to_datetime(date), line_width=1, line_dash="dot", line_color="red")
    fig.add_annotation(
        x=pd.to_datetime(date),
        y=rbc_reset['Close_RY.TO'].max() * 0.95,
        text=label,
        showarrow=True,
        arrowhead=1,
        ax=0,
        ay=-40,
        font=dict(size=9, color="red"),
        textangle=90
    )

# Final layout
fig.update_layout(
    title='RBC Stock Price with Economic Events: 20042024',
    xaxis_title='Date',
    yaxis_title='Price (CAD)',
    hovermode='x unified',
    template='plotly_white',
    width=1100,
    height=600
)

fig.show()

import pandas as pd

# Add economic event annotations and vertical lines
events = {
    '2007-10-09': 'Pre-2008 Market Peak',
    '2008-09-15': 'Lehman Collapse',
    '2009-03-09': '2008 Crash Bottom',
    '2010-05-06': 'Flash Crash',
    '2011-08-05': 'US Credit Downgrade',
    '2014-11-27': 'Oil Price Crash',
    '2015-08-24': 'China Turbulence',
    '2016-06-23': 'Brexit Referendum',
    '2018-02-05': 'VIX Spike',
    '2018-12-24': 'Christmas Selloff',
    '2020-03-23': 'COVID Market Bottom',
    '2020-12-01': 'Vaccine Rollout',
    '2021-11-08': 'Inflation Rises',
    '2022-03-16': 'Fed Hikes Begin',
    '2023-03-10': 'SVB Collapse',
    '2023-10-01': 'BoC Holds Rates',
    '2024-04-01': 'Inflation Cooling'
}

# Re-add vertical lines and annotations
for date, label in events.items():
    fig.add_vline(x=pd.to_datetime(date), line_width=1, line_dash="dot", line_color="red")
    fig.add_annotation(
        x=pd.to_datetime(date),
        y=rbc_reset['Close_RY.TO'].max() * 0.95,
        text=label,
        showarrow=True,
        arrowhead=1,
        ax=0,
        ay=-40,
        font=dict(size=9, color="red"),
        textangle=90
    )

fig.show()
